President Cyril Ramaphosa has arrived at the home of Uyinene Mrwetyana in Buffalo City, Eastern Cape to pay his respects following the tragic killing of Uyinene last week at the hands of a Post Office employee. On Thurday, Ramaphosa urged the nation to "once again, work together to end the violence against the women and children of our country.Â Let us build the South Africa we want, and which all our people so richly deserve." 